<div><h3>FREN 120 - Ways of Writing and Speaking </h3>  <p><hr>This course is an introduction to advanced levels of French and exposes students to some of the areas of study they will find in the French and Francophone Studies program. The course seeks to develop students&#8217; writing and speaking skills through readings, discussion in class, and writing assignments targeting various styles and registers. Typical theme units include poetry and song; news and the media; film and comics.</p>

<p><br>
<br>
 <br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=26&coid=85795" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=26&coid=85795&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=26&coid=85795&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt5760" target="_blank">FREN 106</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span>   or equivalent; AP French language; or permission. <br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> LP<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Annually<br><br><strong>Placement Guidelines</strong><br> Please visit the <a href="http://www.clarku.edu/departments/foreign/undergraduate/placement.cfm" target="_blank">Department of Language, Literature and Culture</a> for the language placement guidelines.<br><br></p><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt5760"></div></div>		</td>
